text: Sadia Nadeem Malik (; born 1 April 1967) is a Pakistani politician who was a Member of the Provincial Assembly of the Punjab, from May 2013 to May 2018. ==Early life and education== She was born on 1 April 1967 in Lahore. She received the degree of Master of Arts in Political Science in 1991 from Government College, Lahore. ==Political career== She was elected to the Provincial Assembly of the Punjab as a candidate of Pakistan Muslim League (N) (PML-N) on a reserved seat for women in 2013 Pakistani general election. She was re-elected to the Provincial Assembly of the Punjab as a candidate of PML-N on a reserved seat for women in 2018 Pakistani general election. ==References== Category:Living people Category:Women members of the Provincial Assembly of the Punjab Category:Punjab MPAs 2013–2018 Category:1967 births Category:Pakistan Muslim League (N) MPAs (Punjab) Category:21st-century women politicians
title: Sadia Nadeem Malik
